Revision history for DBIO-PostgreSQL-Async

{{$NEXT}}
    - Async PostgreSQL storage via EV::Pg (bypasses DBI, uses libpq directly)
    - DBIO::PostgreSQL::Async::Storage with select/insert/update/delete async
    - Transaction support via txn_do_async (BEGIN/COMMIT/ROLLBACK chain)
    - Pipeline mode for batching queries in single round-trip
    - LISTEN/NOTIFY for real-time event streaming
    - COPY IN for bulk data loading
    - Connection pool with transaction pinning
    - Sync fallback (->all, ->first etc. still work via blocking ->get)
    - Prepared statement caching
    - Integration tested against PostgreSQL 18.3
